.TH man 3 "12 July 2022" "0.01" "_printf man page"
.SH NAME
.B _printf
- This is a locally generated funtion that works like the C printf function
.SH SYNOPSIS
The use of this funtion applies when the directive #include "main.h" is used
In the function, 'format' is a character string with zero or more directives
.SH DESCRIPTION
_printf() is a function that prints output according to a format as specified
below. The function writes output on the standard output stream, stdout.
.SH
When using _printf() function you have to use characters preceded by % symbol.
.RS 3
%c: Used when printing characters
.RS 0
%s: Used when printing strings
.RS 0
%d: Used when printing integers of type int that have max or min size
.RS 0
%i: Used when printing integers of type int that have max or min size
.RS 0
%b: Used when printing a number in binary format
.SH RETURN VALUES
The _printf() returns the number of characters printed excluding the null byte
used to end output to strings
.SH SEE ALSO
.I printf(3)
.SH BUGS
No known bugs.
.SH AUTHOR
Wamata Muriu
